abstract: Last evening Rev. GEORGE LANSING TAYLOR preached at the Allen-street M. E. Church on the "Missionary History of Methodism." abstract: CARTER.--On Thursday evening, Feb. 21, 1870, PHEBE, relict of the late Sawyer Carter, aged 84 years. The friends of the family, and of her sons, Jacob S. and Henry C. Carter, and her daughter, Mrs. Harriet B. Jones, are respectfully invited to attend her funeral on Monday, 28th inst., at 12 o'clock, at her late residence, No. 212 West 15th-St. Her remains will be taken to Trinity Cemetery for interment.

abstract: From the San Francisco Bulletin. Deer, antelope, bear and elk constitute the large game of California.
